&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen within the Gynaecology Outpatient department for a new Nurse Associate. This will be the first Nurse Associate post within the Trust.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The position will require you to work alongside a range of healthcare assistants, specialist nurses and consultants to provide exemplary care to the residents of Liverpool and wider community in relation to gynaecology and fertility diagnostics, treatments and aftercare. You will also be expected to provide support for patients and clinicians in clinic consultations and diagnostic procedures.&lt;br /&gt;The successful candidate will be an enthusiastic, motivated and forward thinking individual who will be passionate and committed to delivering excellent standards of clinical care and patient experience.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will work as part of a team and support the organisation and operational management of clinics. The post holder will be an ambassador for the 6 Cs culture for Care, Compassion, Competence, Communication, Commitment and Courage.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
